<br>
1.  Back off completely and see what happens.  Iraq would either implode at which point it would be easier to implement option 2 or it would become more moderate and less of a threat.  This is what we did with Iran.  It works, but very slowly.  (not saying Iran is a peace loving moderate, only that they are slowly becoming less of a threat).<br>
<br>
2.  Go in, dismantle the Iraqi regime piece by piece.  Accept the losses that a fully commited land war will bring.  Accept the resource expenditure that a rebuilding of Iraq will bring.  Spend 10 to 20 years there helping them become a nation again as a rebuilding force, not an occupation force.<br>
<br>
I'm voting for option 2 since it has better odds of succeeding.  However, I don't think our government is willing to commit to it.  Their approval ratings will sink the moment the US populace realizes we may lose more than a few &quot;TV heros&quot;.  <br>
