<br>
The problems I see with allowing Iraq to self-destruct internally through decades of sanctions are numerous.  First of all, the obvious problem is that there's no guarantee that Hussein won't simply continue concentrating on his personal agenda while his people die slowly--his actions over the past decade support this.  <br>
<br>
Secondly, I don't know that the approach is necessarily a viable one, anyway.  Yes, it ultimately did work for Russia, because we were able to halt their aggressive efforts to secure countries full of resources that they needed to survive and thrive through armed conflicts.  Now we're left with a gigantic region filled with disenfranchised drunks basically being run by disparate pockets of organized crime.  That's obviously a generalization, but the kernel of truth is there.  Compare that to Germany and Japan, who were defeated soundly in war and then allowed to rebuild with our help, and it's hard to convince me that the former approach is necessarily better than the latter.  Sure, in the short-term less lives are lost, but the long-term benefits don't justify it in my opinion.  Let me reiterate:  in my opinion. <br>
<br>
Sunmina is right--it can't be a half-assed &quot;policing action&quot; if it's going to succeed on all fronts.  It has to be an all out invasion, which I think Bush has been trying very hard to prepare the American people for that eventuality.  Unfortunately, the jury of popular opinion isn't convinced, with good reason.  These kinds of decisions are the hardest to make, but based on history and everything that I've personally seen, a decisive and committed invasion is the best answer.  Otherwise we're opening ourselves and the rest of the free world up to several years of cultural and economic extortion by underindustrialized countries with incredibly weak economies but who happen to be capable of mass destruction.  <br>
<br>
That's my opinion, nothing more, and I'm only one voter.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=435.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=435.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=435.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=435.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=435.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=435.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a> <b>7</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showPrevMessage?topicID=435.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showNextMessage?topicID=435.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=435.topic&index=129><img src=http://www.pwshift.com/tr/images/mt/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.emailToFriend?topicID=435.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.threadControl?topicID=435.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/posticons/techops.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=435.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.unsu